{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":670,"text":"Evidence suggests that humans in all ages and from all cultures"},{"time":5336,"text":"create their identity in some kind of narrative form."},{"time":9486,"text":"From mother to daughter, preacher to congregant,"},{"time":12227,"text":"teacher to pupil, storyteller to audience."},{"time":15291,"text":"Whether in cave paintings"},{"time":17081,"text":"or the latest uses of the Internet,"},{"time":19711,"text":"human beings have always told their histories and truths"},{"time":23542,"text":"through parable and fable."},{"time":25999,"text":"We are inveterate storytellers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":29476,"text":"But where, in our increasingly secular and fragmented world,"},{"time":33859,"text":"do we offer communality of experience,"},{"time":37957,"text":"unmediated by our own furious consumerism?"},{"time":42307,"text":"And what narrative, what history,"},{"time":45807,"text":"what identity, what moral code"},{"time":48488,"text":"are we imparting to our young?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":51840,"text":"Cinema is arguably"},{"time":54722,"text":"the 20th century's most influential art form."},{"time":57307,"text":"Its artists told stories"},{"time":59357,"text":"across national boundaries,"},{"time":60639,"text":"in as many languages, genres and philosophies"},{"time":63507,"text":"as one can imagine."},{"time":64757,"text":"Indeed, it is hard to find a subject"},{"time":67389,"text":"that film has yet to tackle."},{"time":69406,"text":"During the last decade"},{"time":71057,"text":"we've seen a vast integration of global media,"},{"time":73473,"text":"now dominated by a culture of the Hollywood blockbuster."},{"time":76857,"text":"We are increasingly offered a diet"},{"time":79273,"text":"in which sensation, not story, is king."},{"time":82757,"text":"What was common to us all 40 years ago --"},{"time":85190,"text":"the telling of stories between generations --"},{"time":87989,"text":"is now rarified."},{"time":90074,"text":"As a filmmaker, it worried me."},{"time":92322,"text":"As a human being, it puts the fear of God in me."},{"time":96189,"text":"What future could the young build"},{"time":98606,"text":"with so little grasp"},{"time":99973,"text":"of where they've come from"},{"time":101757,"text":"and so few narratives of what's possible?"},{"time":104815,"text":"The irony is palpable;"},{"time":106463,"text":"technical access has never been greater,"},{"time":109964,"text":"cultural access never weaker."}]},{"cues":[{"time":113031,"text":"And so in 2006 we set up FILMCLUB,"},{"time":117364,"text":"an organization that ran weekly film screenings in schools"},{"time":121399,"text":"followed by discussions."},{"time":123481,"text":"If we could raid the annals of 100 years of film,"},{"time":127214,"text":"maybe we could build a narrative"},{"time":129282,"text":"that would deliver meaning"},{"time":130830,"text":"to the fragmented and restless world of the young."},{"time":133913,"text":"Given the access to technology,"},{"time":135516,"text":"even a school in a tiny rural hamlet"},{"time":139247,"text":"could project a DVD onto a white board."}]},{"cues":[{"time":142948,"text":"In the first nine months"},{"time":144782,"text":"we ran 25 clubs across the U.K.,"},{"time":147130,"text":"with kids in age groups between five and 18"},{"time":150198,"text":"watching a film uninterrupted for 90 minutes."},{"time":153230,"text":"The films were curated and contextualized."},{"time":156114,"text":"But the choice was theirs,"},{"time":157865,"text":"and our audience quickly grew"},{"time":159681,"text":"to choose the richest and most varied diet that we could provide."},{"time":163914,"text":"The outcome, immediate."},{"time":166713,"text":"It was an education of the most profound and transformative kind."},{"time":172299,"text":"In groups as large as 150 and as small as three,"},{"time":175631,"text":"these young people discovered new places,"},{"time":178347,"text":"new thoughts, new perspectives."},{"time":180264,"text":"By the time the pilot had finished,"},{"time":182398,"text":"we had the names of a thousand schools"},{"time":185231,"text":"that wished to join."}]},{"cues":[{"time":189050,"text":"The film that changed my life"},{"time":190671,"text":"is a 1951 film by Vittorio De Sica, \"Miracle in Milan.\""},{"time":195638,"text":"It's a remarkable comment"},{"time":197391,"text":"on slums, poverty and aspiration."},{"time":200721,"text":"I had seen the film on the occasion of my father's 50th birthday."},{"time":204955,"text":"Technology then meant we had to hire a viewing cinema,"},{"time":208917,"text":"find and pay for the print and the projectionist."},{"time":211894,"text":"But for my father,"},{"time":213566,"text":"the emotional and artistic importance of De Sica's vision was so great"},{"time":219352,"text":"that he chose to celebrate his half-century"},{"time":221983,"text":"with his three teenage children and 30 of their friends,"},{"time":225848,"text":"\"In order,\" he said,"},{"time":227200,"text":"\"to pass the baton of concern and hope"},{"time":230667,"text":"on to the next generation.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":233150,"text":"In the last shot of \"Miracle in Milan,\""},{"time":235917,"text":"slum-dwellers float skyward on flying brooms."},{"time":239867,"text":"Sixty years after the film was made"},{"time":242399,"text":"and 30 years after I first saw it,"},{"time":244600,"text":"I see young faces tilt up in awe,"},{"time":247150,"text":"their incredulity matching mine."},{"time":249418,"text":"And the speed with which they associate it"},{"time":251916,"text":"with \"Slumdog Millionaire\" or the favelas in Rio"},{"time":255540,"text":"speaks to the enduring nature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258488,"text":"In a FILMCLUB season about democracy and government,"},{"time":261605,"text":"we screened \"Mr. Smith Goes to Washington.\""},{"time":263521,"text":"Made in 1939, the film is older than most of our members' grandparents."},{"time":269940,"text":"Frank Capra's classic values independence and propriety."},{"time":274081,"text":"It shows how to do right,"},{"time":275640,"text":"how to be heroically awkward."},{"time":277374,"text":"It is also an expression of faith"},{"time":280124,"text":"in the political machine as a force of honor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":283649,"text":"Shortly after \"Mr. Smith\" became a FILMCLUB classic,"},{"time":287132,"text":"there was a week of all-night filibustering in the House of Lords."},{"time":291798,"text":"And it was with great delight"},{"time":293082,"text":"that we found young people up and down the country"},{"time":295733,"text":"explaining with authority"},{"time":297566,"text":"what filibustering was"},{"time":299582,"text":"and why the Lords might defy their bedtime on a point of principle."},{"time":305099,"text":"After all, Jimmy Stewart filibustered for two entire reels."}]},{"cues":[{"time":309233,"text":"In choosing \"Hotel Rwanda,\""},{"time":312300,"text":"they explored genocide of the most brutal kind."},{"time":315583,"text":"It provoked tears as well as incisive questions"},{"time":319116,"text":"about unarmed peace-keeping forces"},{"time":320916,"text":"and the double-dealing of a Western society"},{"time":323599,"text":"that picks its moral fights with commodities in mind."},{"time":327533,"text":"And when \"Schindler's List\" demanded that they never forget,"},{"time":331599,"text":"one child, full of the pain of consciousness, remarked,"},{"time":335716,"text":"\"We already forgot,"},{"time":336985,"text":"otherwise how did 'Hotel Rwanda' happen?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":340999,"text":"As they watch more films their lives got palpably richer."},{"time":344766,"text":"\"Pickpocket\" started a debate about criminality disenfranchisement."},{"time":349399,"text":"\"To Sir, with Love\" ignited its teen audience."},{"time":353266,"text":"They celebrated a change in attitude"},{"time":355915,"text":"towards non-white Britons,"},{"time":357615,"text":"but railed against our restless school system"},{"time":361035,"text":"that does not value collective identity,"},{"time":364083,"text":"unlike that offered by Sidney Poitier's careful tutelage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":370150,"text":"By now, these thoughtful, opinionated, curious young people"},{"time":374265,"text":"thought nothing of tackling films of all forms --"},{"time":377100,"text":"black and white, subtitled,"},{"time":378415,"text":"documentary, non-narrative, fantasy --"},{"time":381149,"text":"and thought nothing of writing detailed reviews"},{"time":383848,"text":"that competed to favor one film over another"},{"time":387332,"text":"in passionate and increasingly sophisticated prose."},{"time":391156,"text":"Six thousand reviews each school week"},{"time":394322,"text":"vying for the honor of being review of the week."}]},{"cues":[{"time":398840,"text":"From 25 clubs, we became hundreds, then thousands,"},{"time":402900,"text":"until we were nearly a quarter of a million kids"},{"time":405982,"text":"in 7,000 clubs right across the country."},{"time":409398,"text":"And although the numbers were, and continue to be, extraordinary,"},{"time":412282,"text":"what became more extraordinary"},{"time":414565,"text":"was how the experience of critical and curious questioning"},{"time":418115,"text":"translated into life."},{"time":420633,"text":"Some of our kids started talking with their parents,"},{"time":423500,"text":"others with their teachers,"},{"time":425266,"text":"or with their friends."},{"time":426249,"text":"And those without friends"},{"time":427949,"text":"started making them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":430150,"text":"The films provided communality across all manner of divide."},{"time":435466,"text":"And the stories they held provided a shared experience."},{"time":438583,"text":"\"Persepolis\" brought a daughter closer to her Iranian mother,"},{"time":443000,"text":"and \"Jaws\" became the way in which one young boy"},{"time":446801,"text":"was able to articulate the fear he'd experienced"},{"time":450366,"text":"in flight from violence"},{"time":451916,"text":"that killed first his father then his mother,"},{"time":454900,"text":"the latter thrown overboard on a boat journey."}]},{"cues":[{"time":459782,"text":"Who was right, who wrong?"},{"time":461741,"text":"What would they do under the same conditions?"},{"time":463857,"text":"Was the tale told well?"},{"time":465406,"text":"Was there a hidden message?"},{"time":467007,"text":"How has the world changed? How could it be different?"},{"time":469740,"text":"A tsunami of questions flew out of the mouths of children"},{"time":474624,"text":"who the world didn't think were interested."},{"time":476374,"text":"And they themselves had not known they cared."},{"time":479845,"text":"And as they wrote and debated,"},{"time":481757,"text":"rather than seeing the films as artifacts,"},{"time":484723,"text":"they began to see themselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":489789,"text":"I have an aunt who is a wonderful storyteller."},{"time":492954,"text":"In a moment she can invoke images"},{"time":495108,"text":"of running barefoot on Table Mountain and playing cops and robbers."},{"time":499073,"text":"Quite recently she told me"},{"time":500639,"text":"that in 1948, two of her sisters and my father"},{"time":504038,"text":"traveled on a boat to Israel without my grandparents."},{"time":506686,"text":"When the sailors mutinied at sea in a demand for humane conditions,"},{"time":511152,"text":"it was these teenagers that fed the crew."},{"time":514886,"text":"I was past 40 when my father died."},{"time":517036,"text":"He never mentioned that journey."}]},{"cues":[{"time":519588,"text":"My mother's mother left Europe in a hurry"},{"time":523273,"text":"without her husband, but with her three-year-old daughter"},{"time":526670,"text":"and diamonds sewn into the hem of her skirt."},{"time":530501,"text":"After two years in hiding,"},{"time":531785,"text":"my grandfather appeared in London."},{"time":534619,"text":"He was never right again."},{"time":536919,"text":"And his story was hushed as he assimilated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":541620,"text":"My story started in England"},{"time":545558,"text":"with a clean slate and the silence of immigrant parents."},{"time":549821,"text":"I had \"Anne Frank,\" \"The Great Escape,\""},{"time":551972,"text":"\"Shoah,\" \"Triumph of the Will.\""},{"time":554486,"text":"It was Leni Riefenstahl"},{"time":556541,"text":"in her elegant Nazi propaganda"},{"time":559324,"text":"who gave context to what the family had to endure."},{"time":563232,"text":"These films held what was too hurtful to say out loud,"},{"time":568882,"text":"and they became more useful to me"},{"time":571232,"text":"than the whispers of survivors"},{"time":573949,"text":"and the occasional glimpse of a tattoo"},{"time":576884,"text":"on a maiden aunt's wrist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":579732,"text":"Purists may feel that fiction dissipates"},{"time":582515,"text":"the quest of real human understanding,"},{"time":585516,"text":"that film is too crude"},{"time":587015,"text":"to tell a complex and detailed history,"},{"time":589449,"text":"or that filmmakers always serve drama over truth."},{"time":593699,"text":"But within the reels lie purpose and meaning."},{"time":596833,"text":"As one 12-year-old said after watching \"Wizard of Oz,\""},{"time":600100,"text":"\"Every person should watch this,"},{"time":602399,"text":"because unless you do"},{"time":604249,"text":"you may not know that you too have a heart.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":608916,"text":"We honor reading, why not honor watching with the same passion?"},{"time":613315,"text":"Consider \"Citizen Kane\" as valuable as Jane Austen."},{"time":616609,"text":"Agree that \"Boyz n the Hood,\" like Tennyson,"},{"time":619808,"text":"offers an emotional landscape and a heightened understanding"},{"time":623826,"text":"that work together."},{"time":625575,"text":"Each a piece of memorable art,"},{"time":627109,"text":"each a brick in the wall of who we are."},{"time":630558,"text":"And it's okay if we remember Tom Hanks"},{"time":633425,"text":"better than astronaut Jim Lovell"},{"time":635475,"text":"or have Ben Kingsley's face superimposed onto that of Gandhi's."},{"time":640039,"text":"And though not real, Eve Harrington, Howard Beale, Mildred Pierce"},{"time":643595,"text":"are an opportunity to discover"},{"time":646292,"text":"what it is to be human,"},{"time":648708,"text":"and no less helpful to understanding our life and times"},{"time":652742,"text":"as Shakespeare is in illuminating the world of Elizabethan England."}]},{"cues":[{"time":658492,"text":"We guessed that film,"},{"time":660060,"text":"whose stories are a meeting place"},{"time":662059,"text":"of drama, music, literature and human experience,"},{"time":664288,"text":"would engage and inspire the young people participating in FILMCLUB."},{"time":668793,"text":"What we could not have foreseen"},{"time":670325,"text":"was the measurable improvements"},{"time":671958,"text":"in behavior, confidence and academic achievement."},{"time":675676,"text":"Once-reluctant students now race to school, talk to their teachers,"},{"time":679958,"text":"fight, not on the playground,"},{"time":681443,"text":"but to choose next week's film --"},{"time":683576,"text":"young people who have found self-definition, ambition"},{"time":687162,"text":"and an appetite for education and social engagement"},{"time":691409,"text":"from the stories they have witnessed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":694375,"text":"Our members defy the binary description"},{"time":697758,"text":"of how we so often describe our young."},{"time":700576,"text":"They are neither feral nor myopically self-absorbed."},{"time":705559,"text":"They are, like other young people,"},{"time":707326,"text":"negotiating a world with infinite choice,"},{"time":710793,"text":"but little culture of how to find meaningful experience."},{"time":715493,"text":"We appeared surprised at the behaviors"},{"time":718127,"text":"of those who define themselves"},{"time":720125,"text":"by the size of the tick on their shoes,"},{"time":722326,"text":"yet acquisition has been the narrative we have offered."}]},{"cues":[{"time":726575,"text":"If we want different values"},{"time":728392,"text":"we have to tell a different story,"},{"time":731859,"text":"a story that understands that an individual narrative"},{"time":735861,"text":"is an essential component of a person's identity,"},{"time":739724,"text":"that a collective narrative"},{"time":741493,"text":"is an essential component of a cultural identity,"},{"time":745474,"text":"and without it it is impossible to imagine yourself"},{"time":749208,"text":"as part of a group."},{"time":750609,"text":"Because when these people get home"},{"time":753665,"text":"after a screening of \"Rear Window\""},{"time":756184,"text":"and raise their gaze to the building next door,"},{"time":758933,"text":"they have the tools to wonder who, apart from them,"},{"time":762598,"text":"is out there"},{"time":764165,"text":"and what is their story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":766698,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":768349,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}